	<h3 class="left-20p">INTERCESSION OBJECTIVES for 2014:</h3><br/>
		<p class="bottom-10">1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	Require every official JSOS CC member ( Kapamuso) to join a monthly Saturday intercession group before the end of March</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">2.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Totally support the Prayer Department in their activities and programs</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">3.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 	Make official church prayer boxes and pouches for distribution among intercessors and prayer groups</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">4.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Require every department to make their official department prayer list and leaflet</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">5.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make an official Answered Prayer Bulletin Board</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">6.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Write and print leaflets on prayer</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">7.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Intensify our involvement to trans-denominational intercessions like the “ International Day of Prayer for the Persecuted Church “ </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">8.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hold intercessors seminars and workshop at least once a year </p>
		
